Simulation development for autonomous robotsand unmanned surface vehicles;
 Integration for standard sensor models, i.e., 3D LiDAR, camera, GPS/IMU, Radar, sonar, etc.;
 Explore cost map and mapping techniques to achieve a certain level of mapping of the environment in 3D space;
 Realization of algorithms developed into computational footprints needed for practical use in robots;
 Tasks encompassing the design, code, debug, test, and documentation phases for web browser (both Mobile and Desktop) based applications;
 Building and deployment REST APIs, develop backend servers and databases for functionality;
 Implementation, system integration, data collection, testing, debugging and trial deployment to deliver functioning modules for various use cases.
 MSc or BSc in Computer Science, or equivalent
 Strong software development in C/C++, Python, Java.
 Proficiency in 3D Engine
 Familiarity with one or more frontend framework, i.e. HTML5, CSS, JavaScript.
 Knowledge and experience with REST APIs.
 Good knowledge on Linux, ROS & Gazebo simulation.
 Good understanding of computer vision, deep learning, fusion algorithms and libraries including OpenCV, SLAM, Pointcloud, Tracking filters.
 Familiarity with robotic navigation, perception and system integration.
 Strong passion and keen to pursue deeper knowledge in AI and robotics.
 Hardworking, dedicated, good communication skill, a team player, resourceful and independent in resolving challenges faced.

